verses.verse: O God, how long will the adversary reproach? Will the enemy blaspheme Your name forever?
(Lam. 2:3) Why do You withdraw Your hand, even Your right hand? Take it out of Your bosom and destroy them.
For (Ps. 44:4) God is my King from of old, Working salvation in the midst of the earth.
(Ex. 14:21) You divided the sea by Your strength; You broke the heads of the sea serpents in the waters.
You broke the heads of Leviathan in pieces, And gave him as food to the people inhabiting the wilderness.
(Ex. 17:5, 6; Num. 20:11; Ps. 105:41; Is. 48:21) You broke open the fountain and the flood; (Ex. 14:21, 22; Josh. 2:10; 3:13) You dried up mighty rivers.
The day is Yours, the night also is (Job 38:12) Yours; (Gen. 1:14-18) You have prepared the light and the sun.
You have (Deut. 32:8; Acts 17:26) set all the borders of the earth; (Gen. 8:22) You have made summer and winter.
Remember this, that the enemy has reproached, O LORD, And that a foolish people has blasphemed Your name.
Oh, do not deliver the life of Your turtledove to the wild beast! Do not forget the life of Your poor forever.
